  "response": "Here are some interesting facts about Indian currency:\n\n1. First Currency Notes:\n- The first paper currency in India was issued by the British in 1861\n- Before that, different regions used various forms of currency\n\n2. Currency Design:\n- Indian currency notes feature quotes from Mahatma Gandhi\n- Gandhi's portrait is on most denomination notes\n- Notes are printed in Hindi and English\n\n3. Unique Features:\n- Indian notes have different sizes for each denomination\n- Visually impaired people can identify notes by size\n- Notes have Braille-like markings for accessibility\n\n4. Historical Changes:\n- After demonetization in 2016, \u20b9500 and \u20b91000 notes were replaced\n- New \u20b92000 notes were introduced temporarily\n- Later withdrawn from circulation in 2018\n\n5. Security Features:\n- Modern notes have multiple security threads\n- Microtext and color-changing ink\n- Watermarks and holographic strips\n\n6. Interesting Trivia:\n- \u20b91 note is still legal tender but rarely used\n- The Reserve Bank of India manages currency production\n- Currency notes are made from special cotton paper\n\n7. Symbolic Representations:\n- Notes depict important national monuments\n- Represent India's cultural and historical heritage\n\nThese facts highlight the complexity and significance of Indian currency.",
